Martyn Uzzell was killed during a charity ride from Land's End to John O'Groats . 
  He was thrown into path of a car by a four-inch deep pothole on the A65 near Giggleswick . 
  North Yorkshire County Council inspected the hole in the weeks before his death but decided it did not need repairing . 
  His widow Kate has now received a six-figure payout from the council . 
  Coroner ruled the state of the road was 'the cause of the incident'